SIMPLE: senseless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Senseless
<hw>Sense"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Destitute of, deficient in, or
contrary to, sense; without sensibility or feeling; unconscious; stupid;
foolish; unwise; unreasonable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You blocks, you stones, you worse than <qex>senseless</qex>
things.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The ears are <qex>senseless</qex> that should give us hearing.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>senseless</qex> grave feels not your pious sorrows.</q>
<rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were a <qex>senseless</qex>, stupid race.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They would repent this their <qex>senseless</qex> perverseness
when it would be too late.</q> <rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sense"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sense"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensibility</ent>⟦br⟧
